    "comment": "Rationale: Fig 4E-G: In quantitation of immunoelectron microscopy images of isolated rat brain synapses (synaptosomes), latrophilin 1 is predominantly found presynaptically near or on the synaptic cleft, while its ligand Lasso is found postsynaptically.\nFig 4H-I: Synaptic biochemical fractions were separated into presynaptic and postsynaptic fractions, which confirmed presynaptic localization of latrophilin 1.\nFig 5: Latrophilin expressed in HEK293 cells and cocultured with rat neurons induced postsynaptic PSD95 clustering in en passent neuronal dendrites suggesting a presynaptic localization and function for latrophilin 1\n\nTogether with the amino acid sequence this strongly suggest that latrophilin 1 is an integral component of the presynaptic membrane.\n\n12/10/2018 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: - LPH1 constructs (accession nos. JF784349-JF784356) were produced from rat cDNA for LPH1\n- Rat brain lysate was used for biochemistry\n- Hippocampal neurons were isolated from P0-P2 rats",
